description.et:
A - the student has an excellent command of the skills and knowledge needed to initiate and draft a project and to solve diverse issues related to project management;
B - the student has a very good command of the skills and knowledge needed to initiate and draft a project and to solve most common issues related to project management;
C - the student has a good command of the skills and knowledge needed to initiate a project and to analyse and solve simpler issues related to project management;
D - the student has acquired at least half of the study outcomes; the student knows the principles of project management and is able to participate in a project as a member of the team;
E - the student has acquired some of the study outcomes; the analysis of issues related to project management is incomplete and the solutions offered are insufficient or irrelevant.
